{
  "stem": "3331.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But if you speak about depriving them of businesses-- not to let them be doctors and lawyers-- then, he said-- then-- then, he said, 'owszem.' It means 'by all means.' So this-- we felt that all those things started-- started to-- all those things started to change.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And with the influence of Germany-- and Poland made a pact.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't know if you know about it, that in 1939, Poland make a pact with Germany, when Germany took over Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the Germans were very shrewd.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they came to Portland, and there was a sliver-- there was a small piece of land.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we called it Zaolzie, because-- this was in southern Poland-- because there was a river, Olza.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And behind the Olza was a small piece of land, and once it belonged to Poland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So Germany made a pact with Poland, and they said we-- a nonaggression pact.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they said, we allow you to take Olza.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So when Germany took Czechoslovakia, Poland took this piece of land, which we Jews saw that this is a trick, and it was a very big mistake.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So Poland was, in this time, together with Germany.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Till the war, till the September-- before September-- and naturally, in October-- in August, when we find out about the treaty from Ribbentrop and Molotov.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we knew that the end is here.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we-- no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't do anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Also, I-- I may-- I must explain that you asked, for the Jews, if the situation changed.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The situation changed very much, because in this time the Polish people started to organize in different cooperatives and businesses.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'38, '39.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the most-- biggest-- first they started with the villages.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And right away, in each village, they had a cooperative of peasants.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
